# Adversary fixture: FM3-a — Unicode escape with uppercase hex digits
# Hypothesis: both \u00E9 and \u00e9 must decode to the same literal
#   (U+00E9, LATIN SMALL LETTER E WITH ACUTE).  A parser storing the raw
#   escape form rather than the decoded code point will diverge.
# Expected outcome: accept, literal value = é (U+00E9)
outcome: accept
fact-count: 1
object-value: "\u00E9" decoded to U+00E9 (é)
divergence-hypothesis: ObjectMismatch — raw-escape storage vs decoded storage
spec-ref: W3C RDF 1.1 N-Triples §2.3 UCHAR + HEX productions (case-insensitive)
